ethics & war reporting guantanamo america's experiment in extraterritorial detention with carol rosenberg journalist events at stanford ethics & war reporting guantanamo america's experiment in extraterritorial detention with carol rosenberg journalist facebook twitter email print add to calendar carol rosenberg has covered the proceedings in the us prison camps in guantanamo bay for the miami herald for nine years earlier this year she was awarded the robert f kennedy journalism award which recognizes outstanding reporting on human rights and social justice at the time of her award the rfk center for justice and human rights reported that rosenberg had logged more time at guantanamo than any other reporter taking on the task of ensuring that this important story is not forgotten in this talk rosenberg focuses on the challenges of operating as a journalist in guantanamo bay and the ethical issues that working there entails carol rosenberg when wednesday november 16 2011 4 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where bldg 260 room 113 main quad 450 serra mall stanford ca 94305 usa map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading humanities public service international sponsor knight fellowships program center for ethics in society stanford says no to war contact 650 723 0997 joanbery stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 296 29637 more info last modified november 7 2011
